FBIS4-16125 "drsov072_u_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 Latvia Ulmanis, UK's Major Discuss Agreements Ulmanis, UK's Major Discuss Agreements LD1304153894 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1300 GMT 13 Apr 94 LD1304153894 Riga Radio Riga Network Latvian BFN [Text] Latvian State President Guntis Ulmanis is continuing his visit to Western Europe. Today, the delegation headed by the president met in London with British Prime Minister John Major, Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd, and Douglas Hogg, the minister of state for foreign and commonwealth affairs to explain Latvia's stance and find out the British opinion on the issue of initialled Latvian-Russian agreements and Yeltsin's order of 5 April on the creation of military bases in CIS member states and Latvia. Ulmanis also met David Manning, the director of the eastern department at the Foreign and Commonwealth Office, Roger Bone, an adviser to the foreign secretary on political affairs, and British Ambassador to Latvia Richard Ralph. The delegation will return to Riga at midnight.
